## **Multi-tenant SaaS Architecture**

### **Core Architecture Layers**
1. **Core Layer** (Foundation)
   - Authentication & Authorization System
   - Multi-tenant Data Management
   - **Enterprise Compliance Framework** (see `08_ENTERPRISE_COMPLIANCE_STANDARDS.mdc`)
   - Real-time Communication Infrastructure
   - Performance Monitoring & Analytics

2. **Modules Layer** (Business Logic)
   - Knowledge Management
   - AI Provider Management
   - Project Management
   - Education & Learning
   - Productivity & Analytics

3. **Plugins Layer** (Extensions)
   - Advanced AI Capabilities
   - Third-party Integrations
   - Custom Automation Tools

### **Naming Conventions (MANDATORY)**
- **Core Components**: `Core[Feature][Type]` pattern in `src/core/`
- **Enterprise Components**: `Enterprise[Feature][Type]` pattern
- **Admin Components**: `Admin[Feature][Type]` pattern
- **BANNED Prefixes**: "Enhanced", "Unified", "Advanced"

### **File Structure Standards**
- Follow `CEREBRAL_010_CORE_NAMING_SPECIFICATION.md`
- Use proper barrel exports (`index.ts`)
- Maintain category-based organization
- Check implementation roadmap before assuming missing components

### **Performance Optimization**
- **Lazy Loading**: All components >20KB must use lazy loading
- **Bundle Splitting**: Intelligent chunking for feature-based optimization
- **Tree Shaking**: Enhanced tree shaking with moduleSideEffects: false
- **Minification**: Terser with production-grade compression

### **Security & Compliance**
- **MULTI-STANDARD COMPLIANCE** - See `08_ENTERPRISE_COMPLIANCE_STANDARDS.mdc` for complete requirements:
  - **SOC2 Type II** - Continuous security monitoring and controls
  - **GDPR** - Privacy by design and data protection
  - **ISO27001** - Systematic information security management
  - **HIPAA** - Healthcare data protection (healthcare modules)
  - **Industry Standards** - Automotive (ISO 26262), Legal (ABA), Financial (PCI DSS)
- **Data encryption** - At rest and in transit
- **Access controls** - Role-based permissions and audit trails
- **Security monitoring** - Real-time threat detection

### **Mobile-First PWA Architecture**
- Responsive design for all components
- Offline functionality where applicable
- Native mobile integration capabilities
- Progressive enhancement principles

